# Enhance Seller Dashboard, Supabase Image Uploads & Checkout Logic

This plan outlines the steps to configure Supabase cloud storage for images, wire up the Seller Dashboard to the backend, and restrict checkout address changes.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Supabase Cloud Storage Credentials Required**
> Because you want images to upload directly to Supabase, we need to install the `django-storages` package. However, you will need to create a Storage Bucket in Supabase and provide the keys to the backend. 
> 
> Please confirm you have created a public bucket in Supabase (e.g., named `media`) and have added the following to your `backend/thabuyer_backend/.env` file:
> ```env
> USE_S3=True
> AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your_supabase_s3_access_key
> AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your_supabase_s3_secret_key
> AWS_STORAGE_BUCKET_NAME=your_bucket_name
> AWS_S3_ENDPOINT_URL=https://<project-id>.supabase.co/storage/v1/s3
> AWS_S3_REGION_NAME=your_region
> ```
> *Note: I will write the code to support this, but uploads will fail until you provide these keys in your `.env`.*

